In a uniform client distribution scenario, Î±=0.0ğ›¼0.0\alpha=0.0 and Î²=1.0ğ›½1.0\beta=1.0, the baseline and game base models perform similar accuracy shown table I. In the first experiment,
each client has training data with only 1 class label;
in another experiment,
each client has training data with 2 class labels.
Therefore, not all FL servers can obtain models
trained from the data with most class labels.
Particularly,
if an FL server acquires a small number of clients,
its model is trained based on the data with only a few class labels.
Also, since
clients are randomly selected from the client pool,
an FL server could receive a model updated based on the data with
different number of class labels
in different rounds.
Thus, testing accuracy varies in rounds,
even though they get model updates from the same number of clients.
